value.value: The area that is located between the antennal rims.
The area that is delimited by the ventrally bifurcating central keel.
The foramen that is located on the head in which the radicle is positioned.
The carina that divides the dorsal axillar area into horizontal and vertical areas.
The patch that is less melanized than the surrounding area and is translucent.
The carina that delimits the supraalar area posteriorly.
The sulcus that extends from the mesopleural pit to the mesocoxal articulation.
The line that traverses the mesoscutum and originates from the lateral margin between the antemedian and postmedian notal wing processes.
The carina that delimits the anterior vertical area of abdominal segment 2.
The epipharyngeal muscle that extends between the lateral parts of the sitophore.
The carina that delimits posteriorly the pronotal neck.
The sulcus that corresponds to the anteromedian pronotal ridge.
The area that is located proximally on the femur and is delimited by a groove.
The leg segment that is located proximal to the femur and distal to the coxa.
The sclerite that is located anterolaterally of the coxa and corresponds to the site of insertion of the notal-trochantinal muscle.
The process that is small and knob-like or round.
The verricule that arises from a tubercle.
Sensilla trichodea type I occur on the distal ends [...] of the antennal flagellum.  They have small conical basal sockets with slender and strongly bent shafts.
The aporous sensillum that has a hairlike cuticular component.
The depression that is medially raised and bears medially a seta.
The abscissa that extends anteriorly from the stigmal vein.
The area that is located distomedially on the end of the telotarsus and articulates with pretarsal claws.
The sclerite that corresponds to the site of insertion of the flexor of the pretarsus.
The area that is located dorsally of the ventral margin of the antennal rim and ventrally of the anterior ocellus medial to the inner margins of the eye and malar line.
The carina that traverses the subdorsal mesopleuron.
The ridge that is vertical and extends along the valviceps.
The area that is the distal part of the penisvalva dorsally of the ergot.
The spine that is located on the paravalva.
The area that is located proximally of the ergot on the penisvalva.
The area that is delimited by the vannal veins, or veins that articulates with the third axillary sclerite.
The duct that connect the testis with the ejaculatory duct.
The area that is lamella-like and is located on the calcar.

label.value: ventral apodeme of the first phragma

value.value: The apodeme that is located anterolaterally on the prophragma and corresponds to the site of origin of the third mesopleuro-mesonotal muscle.
The area that connects ventrally the left and right halves of the pronotum.
The carina that is located on the border of the metepisternal depression and the metacoxal depression.

The hypopharyngeal muscle that is unpaired and arises from the median anterior part of the tentorial bridge and inserts on the proximal part of the ventral wall of the cibarium or on the proximal margin of the sitophore, immediately distally to the point where the alimentary canal passes between the lateral arms of the sitophore.
The edge that sets off the ventral vertical lobe of the propleuron from the ventral propleural area.
The ridge that extends ventrally on the posterior part of the tentorial arm.

The area that is more heavily sclerotised than surrounding areas, traverse the mesopostnotum, unites laterally with the dorsal mesopostnotal flange, continuous laterally with the laterophragma and ventrally (posteriorly) with the mesophragma.
The ridge that is located ventrally on the metafurcal arm.
The area that is located on the metapleuron anteroventrally of the metapleural sulcus.
The pharyngeal muscle that arises from the dorsal surface of the tentorial bridge and inserts ventrally on the pharyngeal wall.
The muscle that arises anteriorly from the cranium and inserts on the posterior margin of the prementum.
The ridge that is located ventrally on the profurcal arm and corresponds to the site of origin of the profurco-procoxal muscle.

The postoccipital muscle that arises partly from the anterior surface of the dorsal profurcal lamella ventral to the site of origin of the dorsal profurco-postoccipital muscle and partly from the median area of the dorsal profurcal lamella.
The pit that is located ventrally on the pronotum.
The area that is located ventrally on the propleuron and is delimited laterally by the longitudinal carina of the propleuron.
The carina that separates the metasomal depression from the metacoxal depression.
The ridge that arises medially from the pleurostomal condyle and corresponds to the site of attachment of the labrum.
The row that is composed of spines and is located ventrally on the apex of the calcar.
